itemDescription: Irish nationalist, poet, journalist and 1916 Easter Rising leader

wikipedia_page.main: Joseph Mary Plunkett  (Irish: Seosamh Máire Pluincéid, 21 November 1887 – 4 May 1916) was an Irish nationalist, republican, poet, journalist, revolutionary and a leader of the 1916 Easter Rising. Joseph Mary Plunkett married Grace Gifford in 1916, seven hours before his execution.
